{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/english-to-arabic-better/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Yasser Codes","social":{"twitter":"ysr.sayed","instagram":"yeyeyesser","medium":"theyasser","email":"ysr.sayed@gmail.com"}}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"f2188b92-8fb1-590f-b844-ee98643fb547","excerpt":"You cannot use CSS code you built for an English web page for an Arabic web page. I wrote a post previously about using SCSS to help you manage code for Arabicâ€¦","html":"<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 680px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/aa440/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 25.882352941176467%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Not everything goes as planned when redoing your CSS for Arabic.\"\n        title=\"Not everything goes as planned when redoing your CSS for Arabic.\"\n        src=\"/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/c5bb3/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/04472/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png 170w,\n/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/9f933/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png 340w,\n/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/c5bb3/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png 680w,\n/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/b12f7/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png 1020w,\n/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/b5a09/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png 1360w,\n/static/c21a232e1343597f69b7fe279c43c70c/aa440/1*hyU1RXbyI7CM3WM8iGJV9Q.png 1500w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Not everything goes as planned when redoing your CSS for Arabic.</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>You cannot use CSS code you built for an English web page for an Arabic web page.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I wrote a <a href=\"https://medium.com/meddy-blog/translating-your-front-end-to-arabic-3308a511b560\">post</a> previously about using SCSS to help you manage code for Arabic web pages. Iâ€™ve ran into a couple problems that I was able to solve with absolute elegance. <strong>If anyone reading this post has a better solution to this problem please let me know.</strong></p>\n<h1>Brief Description of the Problem</h1>\n<p>If you are tasked with creating a page that goes from English to Arabic with the click of a button (as seen here on <a href=\"https://www.meddy.com/\">Meddy</a>â€¦ shameless ðŸ”Œ), you might be tempted to create one CSS file for that page and simply reuse it across the two versions of the page. Which makes sense, one file means that youâ€™ll keep your application <strong>DRY</strong> and you can just focus on developing the CSS. This, unfortunately, doesnâ€™t work so well since there are slight differences to the page structures when switching languages.</p>\n<p>The common solution is to create two CSS files; one for English and one for Arabic, and in the Arabic CSS file overwrite parts of the English CSS to fix the inconsistencies.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 674px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6196022f93b132cdbac2ced07a909368/fdaf8/1*DOHzaz39JTfq2J3VuHOG2g.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 45.294117647058826%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"When writing Arabic CSS, you just import and overwrite English CSS.\"\n        title=\"When writing Arabic CSS, you just import and overwrite English CSS.\"\n        src=\"/static/6196022f93b132cdbac2ced07a909368/fdaf8/1*DOHzaz39JTfq2J3VuHOG2g.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6196022f93b132cdbac2ced07a909368/04472/1*DOHzaz39JTfq2J3VuHOG2g.png 170w,\n/static/6196022f93b132cdbac2ced07a909368/9f933/1*DOHzaz39JTfq2J3VuHOG2g.png 340w,\n/static/6196022f93b132cdbac2ced07a909368/fdaf8/1*DOHzaz39JTfq2J3VuHOG2g.png 674w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 674px) 100vw, 674px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">When writing Arabic CSS, you just import and overwrite English CSS.</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>The reason this is a common solution is because itâ€™s extremely tempting to do. Whenever something looks a little awkward in the Arabic page you can just overwrite the English CSS and it will fix it.</p>\n<p>However, this becomes <strong>extremely unmaintainable</strong> very quickly <strong>especially if youâ€™re using</strong> <a href=\"https://www.sitepoint.com/descendant-selector-css-selector/\"><strong>Descendant Selectors</strong></a>. In this post weâ€™ll discuss an elegant convenient solution to tackling this problem.</p>\n<h2>The Problem with Two Files</h2>\n<p>Letâ€™s say we have classes <code class=\"language-text\">.seperate-children</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">.highlight-element</code> defined below.</p>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <div class=\"iframe-wrapper\">\n        <iframe\n            width=\"100%\"\n            height=\"600px\"\n            frameborder=\"0\"\n            scrolling=\"no\"\n            id=\"sizetracker\"\n            src='data:text/html;charset=utf-8,\n            <head><base target=\"_blank\" /></head>\n            <body><script src=\"https://gist.github.com/yelsayed/2ea870e1076f3ab981a2fa6ed3e9c29a.js\"></script>\n            </body>'></iframe>\n    </div>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">\nSample code we use as an example to show bad approach.</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<p>Hereâ€™s some HTML to use the above.</p>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <div class=\"iframe-wrapper\">\n        <iframe\n            width=\"100%\"\n            height=\"180px\"\n            frameborder=\"0\"\n            scrolling=\"no\"\n            id=\"sizetracker\"\n            src='data:text/html;charset=utf-8,\n            <head><base target=\"_blank\" /></head>\n            <body><script src=\"https://gist.github.com/yelsayed/eecef682ec8920c46036095822b7eb6f.js\"></script>\n            </body>'></iframe>\n    </div>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">\nSome HTML to accompany the above CSS.</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<p>This should look like this:</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 566px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2d575aa40d99e51bbf8b2ffe20477f27/6fe44/1*Bw9xxDyIhOibS2hXUyxQJA.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 24.11764705882353%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Output of the above code\"\n        title=\"Output of the above code\"\n        src=\"/static/2d575aa40d99e51bbf8b2ffe20477f27/6fe44/1*Bw9xxDyIhOibS2hXUyxQJA.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2d575aa40d99e51bbf8b2ffe20477f27/04472/1*Bw9xxDyIhOibS2hXUyxQJA.png 170w,\n/static/2d575aa40d99e51bbf8b2ffe20477f27/9f933/1*Bw9xxDyIhOibS2hXUyxQJA.png 340w,\n/static/2d575aa40d99e51bbf8b2ffe20477f27/6fe44/1*Bw9xxDyIhOibS2hXUyxQJA.png 566w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 566px) 100vw, 566px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Output of the above code</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Pretty simple, but remember in Arabic itâ€™s from right to left by adding <code class=\"language-text\">direction: rtl</code> to the HTML. So it would look more like this in the Arabic page.</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 568px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8d6f1c5bad7819679e8716ce5012fb02/10e91/1*TqjMCJ07M_lylrVo68WYCQ.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 23.52941176470588%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Output after flipping direction\"\n        title=\"Output after flipping direction\"\n        src=\"/static/8d6f1c5bad7819679e8716ce5012fb02/10e91/1*TqjMCJ07M_lylrVo68WYCQ.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8d6f1c5bad7819679e8716ce5012fb02/04472/1*TqjMCJ07M_lylrVo68WYCQ.png 170w,\n/static/8d6f1c5bad7819679e8716ce5012fb02/9f933/1*TqjMCJ07M_lylrVo68WYCQ.png 340w,\n/static/8d6f1c5bad7819679e8716ce5012fb02/10e91/1*TqjMCJ07M_lylrVo68WYCQ.png 568w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 568px) 100vw, 568px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Output after flipping direction</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>Which is not the desired effect. An easy way to fix this is make another CSS file for Arabic modifications and add this line to it.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.highlight-element</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">margin-left</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 40px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">margin-right</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> unset<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>But this doesnâ€™t work!</strong> This wonâ€™t do anything. The reason being, <code class=\"language-text\">.separate-children .highlight-element</code> has a higher precedence than .highlight-element. So your code will not apply and youâ€™ll have to either use <code class=\"language-text\">!important</code> (<a href=\"https://j11y.io/css/dont-use-important/\">horrible idea</a>) or write out the entire tag (which is a bad ideaâ€¦ in the long run)</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>But why donâ€™t we just write the full tag Mr. Writer?!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Simply because if youâ€™re dealing with a lot of CSS code then itâ€™s impossible to keep track of the entire sequence of inheritance especially if youâ€™re using <a href=\"https://sass-lang.com/\">SCSS</a> (and if youâ€™re not, then you should), and even if you do it manually youâ€™ll just have a file of weird and impossible to read code. <strong>Just look at this mess!</strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"css\"><pre class=\"language-css\"><code class=\"language-css\"><span class=\"token selector\">.dashboard-navbar, .procedure-master-list-container, .row-actions, .add-element,  \n.back-wrapper, .dashboards-nav-wrapper, footer, .invoice-footer, .no-content, .select-icon.meddy-light-chevron</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">display</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> none<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">.invoice-detail-container, .dashboards-container-wrapper</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">width</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 100% **<span class=\"token important\">!important</span>**<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#mainContainer</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">margin-top</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0 **<span class=\"token important\">!important</span>**<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#invoices .invoice-detail-container .invoice-table .invoice-table-body :not(.date-picker-form) td</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 10px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">padding</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 5px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#invoices .invoice-detail-container .invoice-header</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 14px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#invoices .invoice-detail-container .invoice-table .invoice-table-header th</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 14px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">padding</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 5px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#invoices .invoice-detail-container .invoice-number-input</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 10px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#invoices .invoice-detail-container .assign-invoice .form-control-label</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">font-size</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 10px<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#dashboardIndex .dashboards-container</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">padding-bottom</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>  \n<span class=\"token selector\">#invoices .invoice-detail-container</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>  \n    <span class=\"token property\">margin-bottom</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> 0<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>  \n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>Elegant Solution</h2>\n<p>Instead of overwriting and find the right sequence, it would be better to simply inject the Arabic CSS code in the English CSS code. Think about it, if you have the English CSS and you knew all the places where you should be injecting your code, then youâ€™ll have this new file that is very close to how the Arabic CSS should look like. Hereâ€™s an illustration to help you understand:</p>\n<p><figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 628px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/784518e10296c99ef62183aa290fbffc/3d84d/1*I5FY7kfxWDxtWw8CF1WyDA.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 64.11764705882354%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Basic illustration of the idea I had\"\n        title=\"Basic illustration of the idea I had\"\n        src=\"/static/784518e10296c99ef62183aa290fbffc/3d84d/1*I5FY7kfxWDxtWw8CF1WyDA.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/784518e10296c99ef62183aa290fbffc/04472/1*I5FY7kfxWDxtWw8CF1WyDA.png 170w,\n/static/784518e10296c99ef62183aa290fbffc/9f933/1*I5FY7kfxWDxtWw8CF1WyDA.png 340w,\n/static/784518e10296c99ef62183aa290fbffc/3d84d/1*I5FY7kfxWDxtWw8CF1WyDA.png 628w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 628px) 100vw, 628px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">Basic illustration of the idea I had</figcaption>\n  </figure></p>\n<p>To do this we need to use some SCSS, specifically their <a href=\"https://sass-lang.com/guide\">mixin feature</a>. Hereâ€™s the code for that:</p>\n<figure class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figure\" style=\"\">\n    <div class=\"iframe-wrapper\">\n        <iframe\n            width=\"100%\"\n            height=\"470px\"\n            frameborder=\"0\"\n            scrolling=\"no\"\n            id=\"sizetracker\"\n            src='data:text/html;charset=utf-8,\n            <head><base target=\"_blank\" /></head>\n            <body><script src=\"https://gist.github.com/yelsayed/55dae56b3a6cc80daf63db66e507bbb3.js\"></script>\n            </body>'></iframe>\n    </div>\n    <figcaption class=\"gatsby-resp-image-figcaption\">\nImplementation and usage of the mixin.</figcaption>\n  </figure>\n<h2><strong>Explanation</strong></h2>\n<p>The implementation and usage are explained in the comments in the code above. Basically what the mixin is doing is it takes any piece of code that you give it and injects into the page if the <code class=\"language-text\">$language</code> is set to <code class=\"language-text\">&quot;arabic&quot;</code>. The way you use it is while writing your code normally as if youâ€™re in the English page, you include the <code class=\"language-text\">add-to-arabic</code> mixin and you give it some code to inject it if it were compiling the Arabic page.</p>\n<h2>But Mr. Writer what is $languageâ€¦</h2>\n<p>But Yasser what is this <code class=\"language-text\">$language</code> variable and how do I set it on the Arabic page only? Itâ€™s a <strong>global variable</strong>.</p>\n<p>In your SCSS compiler you have to specify one file to turn from SCSS to CSS, itâ€™s just a simple mapping. If you set the language variable at the top of the file before putting in all the other code, then you have yourself a <strong>global variable</strong>. Hereâ€™s another one of my famous illustrations:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 561px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f96e0017df515e8af0ab55a332aa9d66/410f3/1*MPuPiMMu_p_JZxWpkwEK9Q.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 127.6470588235294%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1 MPuPiMMu p JZxWpkwEK9Q\"\n        title=\"1 MPuPiMMu p JZxWpkwEK9Q\"\n        src=\"/static/f96e0017df515e8af0ab55a332aa9d66/410f3/1*MPuPiMMu_p_JZxWpkwEK9Q.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f96e0017df515e8af0ab55a332aa9d66/04472/1*MPuPiMMu_p_JZxWpkwEK9Q.png 170w,\n/static/f96e0017df515e8af0ab55a332aa9d66/9f933/1*MPuPiMMu_p_JZxWpkwEK9Q.png 340w,\n/static/f96e0017df515e8af0ab55a332aa9d66/410f3/1*MPuPiMMu_p_JZxWpkwEK9Q.png 561w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 561px) 100vw, 561px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>My code is as simple as whatâ€™s in the illustration, and it works like a charm!</p>\n<p>Thanks for reading. Please let me know if you have a better way of doing what you saw above.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Translating your front end to Arabic, a better way","date":"September 30, 2018","description":"I wrote a post previously about using SCSS to help you manage code for Arabic web pages. Iâ€™ve ran into a couple problems that I was able to solve with absolute elegance. If anyone reading this postâ€¦"}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/cache-decorator/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Simple Cache Decorator for Webapps that self-invalidates"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/django/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Software Entomology: Django Primary Key IntegrityError on Object Creation"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"f2188b92-8fb1-590f-b844-ee98643fb547","previousPostId":"b1880dfe-b073-5827-b4a3-aadcaf831f6c","nextPostId":"e400e503-a2d1-566f-b155-7f8390b19b91"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"]}